==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Salience
<hw>Sa"li*ence</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Salient</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The quality or condition of
being salient; a leaping; a springing forward; an assaulting.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The quality or state of projecting, or being
projected; projection; protrusion.</def> <rj><au>Sir W.
Hamilton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Saliency</ent>⟦br⟧
